From: bluecat <lmhtq1991@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 30 May 2026 19:40:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Phase C-6 L50/L51: TLAB allocate + call_VM oop result as capabilities

After push_ptr/pop_ptr (L49), the new/dup/invokespecial receiver had the
right oop ADDRESS but tag-0 — the object itself was tag-0 from `new`. Two
high-leverage sources, both fixed:

L50 BarrierSetAssembler::tlab_allocate: loaded the TLAB top with an
8-byte ldr, so every fast-path-allocated object (and the stored-back top)
was tag-0. cap-LDR the top (the object inherits the TLAB bounds — fine
for correctness) and cap-STR the bumped top.

L51 MacroAssembler::get_vm_result / get_vm_result_2: the call_VM oop
(and metadata) result is read from JavaThread::_vm_result with an 8-byte
ldr → tag-0. This is the SLOW-path `new` object (and every other oop a
runtime call returns: newarray, ldc, resolution, reflection, ...).
cap-LDR both.

RESULT: slow-path `new` objects keep their tags; the invokespecial
<init> runs; execution advances to a new template at 0x428c0ce4 (L52).

Session: 52 commits, 120 build iterations, L25-L51 resolved.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

diff --git a/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/gc/shared/barrierSetAssembler_aarch64.cpp b/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/gc/shared/barrierSetAssembler_aarch64.cpp
index a4a2b142039..c3d40616c07 100644
--- a/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/gc/shared/barrierSetAssembler_aarch64.cpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/gc/shared/barrierSetAssembler_aarch64.cpp
@@ -58,11 +58,23 @@ void BarrierSetAssembler::load_at(MacroAssembler* masm, DecoratorSet decorators,
           __ decode_heap_oop(dst);
         }
       } else {
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+        // C-6 fix #43: an uncompressed oop is a 16-byte capability;
+        // integer ldr strips the tag and any later use of the loaded
+        // oop as a base faults. cap-LDR preserves the cap. High-leverage:
+        // every oop field/array/native load goes through here.
+        __ cap_ldr(dst, src);
+#else
         __ ldr(dst, src);
+#endif
       }
     } else {
       assert(in_native, "why else?");
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+      __ cap_ldr(dst, src);
+#else
       __ ldr(dst, src);
+#endif
     }
     break;
   }
@@ -95,11 +107,22 @@ void BarrierSetAssembler::store_at(MacroAssembler* masm, DecoratorSet decorators
         }
         __ strw(val, dst);
       } else {
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+        // C-6 fix #43: store the full 16-byte oop capability (cap-STR).
+        // val may be zr (null store) — czr writes a null cap, which is
+        // the intended null oop.
+        __ cap_str(val, dst);
+#else
         __ str(val, dst);
+#endif
       }
     } else {
       assert(in_native, "why else?");
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+      __ cap_str(val, dst);
+#else
       __ str(val, dst);
+#endif
     }
     break;
   }
@@ -140,7 +163,17 @@ void BarrierSetAssembler::tlab_allocate(MacroAssembler* masm, Register obj,
 
   // verify_tlab();
 
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+  // C-6 fix #50: the TLAB top is a heap capability; an 8-byte ldr drops
+  // its tag so every TLAB-allocated object (and the stored-back top) is
+  // tag-0, faulting when the object is later used as an oop. cap-LDR the
+  // top (obj inherits the TLAB's bounds — acceptable for correctness),
+  // and cap-STR the bumped top. The tlab_end load stays integer (only
+  // compared by address). High-leverage: all fast-path allocations.
+  __ cap_ldr_imm(obj, rthread, in_bytes(JavaThread::tlab_top_offset()));
+#else
   __ ldr(obj, Address(rthread, JavaThread::tlab_top_offset()));
+#endif
   if (var_size_in_bytes == noreg) {
     __ lea(end, Address(obj, con_size_in_bytes));
   } else {
@@ -151,7 +184,11 @@ void BarrierSetAssembler::tlab_allocate(MacroAssembler* masm, Register obj,
   __ br(Assembler::HI, slow_case);
 
   // update the tlab top pointer
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+  __ cap_str_imm(end, rthread, in_bytes(JavaThread::tlab_top_offset()));
+#else
   __ str(end, Address(rthread, JavaThread::tlab_top_offset()));
+#endif
 
   // recover var_size_in_bytes if necessary
   if (var_size_in_bytes == end) {
diff --git a/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/macroAssembler_aarch64.cpp b/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/macroAssembler_aarch64.cpp
